            <p> Blockchain technology adds new milestones to its endless possibilities. The real-world use cases are
              expanding and disrupting the current systems. It is becoming more transparent and offers users an
              alternative asset class. Blockchain technology applications have influenced a variety of new sectors. </p>
            <p> Worldwide spending on blockchain technologies exceeded $6.6 billion in 2021, and the current year
              anticipates much more investments. Most Blockchain applications are focused on the financial sector due to
              the time and money that blockchain saves. </p>
            <p> Other major tech interest sectors include the entertainment industry, real estate, and the healthcare
              sector. Let us now check how blockchain is simplifying these areas and businesses. </p>

            <h3> Decentralized Finance (DeFi) </h3>
            <p> Decentralized Finance, AKA DeFi is a broad term that includes financial services on the public
              blockchain. They usually are distributed on Ethereum blockchain and work on distributed ledger technology
              such as cryptocurrencies. </p>
            <p> DeFi works with decentralized applications (dApp). Users can download and install this application. You
              don’t need to create accounts, but you have to connect your wallets to transfer money. It helps to
              eliminate third-party intervention in transactions. </p>
            <p> DeFi participants can send their tokens to merchants or other users in no time without waiting for a
              third party's approval. It eliminates intermediary charges and saves time and effort for the user. Crypto
              platforms and dApps enable users to lend and borrow cryptocurrency without paperwork and processing
              delays. Moreover, users can deposit their tokens to earn interest. </p>
            <h3> Smart contracts </h3>
            <p> As the name suggests, these are contracts encoded on blockchain and are automatically executed only when
              the predefined conditions are met. Conditions are coded in the smart contracts as the program with the
              concern of parties involved in the agreement. </p>
            <p> Blockchain smart contracts help business in numerous ways. Self-executing smart contracts enable
              avoiding uncertainty and delays when carrying out the agreement. Hence, they are popular in deals
              involving man and money. Also, ensure increased speed, transparency, error-free execution, and security.
              Below is the primary area where smart contracts are finding their business applications:- </p>
            <ul class="blog-li">
              <li> Insurance agreements </li>
              <li> Multi-signature contracts </li>
              <li> Financial obligations </li>
            </ul>

            <h3> NFT Thunder </h3>
            <p> Nonfungible tokens started soaring in the market in 2021. New NFT projects and tokens began blooming in
              the market. People started investing in their favorite digital art tokens. BAYS, WOW, Boos beauties, and
              crypto punks have emerged as the favorite celebrity NFT tokens. </p>
            <p> The NFT craze skyrocketed, and investors started bidding higher in the NFT marketplaces. An NFT named
              “The Merge” sold $91.8 million last year. The sale of “The Merge” has been marked as the most expensive
              NFT sale in history. NFT run fuels the crypto markets and new NFTs are mushrooming in the arena. Advocates
              envision NFTs will be the future of art and the interest in NFT will eventually increase. </p>
            <img src="~/images/trade-new-blog-2.jpg" alt="~/image">

            <h3> Blockchain real estate </h3>
            <p> Blockchain is bringing a new face to the real estate industry. It helps avoid delays in paperwork,
              face-to-face interactions, and conflicts associated with the global real estate industry. </p>
            <p> Blockchain enables plot listing, comparing plots in one place, and settling the entire transaction. Here
              are some of the benefits of blockchain real estate. </p>
            <ul class="blog-li">
              <li> People can buy a portion of the land or property through blockchain real estate. </li>
              <li> Decentralization drives transparency and reduces third-party intervention. </li>
              <li> It helps to avoid intermediary charges, massive paperwork, and legal constraints. </li>
            </ul>
            <img src="~/images/trade-new-blog-3.jpg" alt="~/image">

            <h3> Metaverse </h3>
            <p> Metaverse is a buzz in the web3 town. From Web2 internet technologies, we are moving to Web3. The
              metaverse is a virtual universe regarded as the third iteration of the internet by proponents. Users
              navigate a virtual world that resembles the real world through technology like virtual reality (VR),
              augmented reality (AR), AI, social media, and digital currency. </p>
            <p> Corporates like Microsoft, Meta, Apple, Decentraland, and Nike are already here. Other brands are trying
              to build projects on Metaverse. </p>
            <img src="~/images/trade-new-blog-4.jpg" alt="~/image">

            <h3> Epilogue </h3>
            <p> Crypto and blockchain are reframing the ways industries are working now. The unending possibilities of
              technology attract new users every day. Mainstream projects are taking an interest in automating their
              processes with the help of blockchain technology. </p>
            <p> One sign of the ever-evolving potential of the digital currency field is the rising popularity of Web3
              and blockchain technology. Stay tuned with TechnoSavvy to know more about the developments and information on
              cryptocurrency and the blockchain niche. </p>

